1
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 14: Charged Per Message]

2
00:01:10,879 --> 00:01:11,912
You're Zhu Ying Tai.

3
00:01:11,912 --> 00:01:12,920
You're Liang Shan Bo.

4
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:14,239
I'm Ma Wen Cai.

5
00:01:14,239 --> 00:01:16,920
And he is our stage producer.

6
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,080
I'm in charge of narration,

7
00:01:18,080 --> 00:01:20,419
stage, sound effects, and props.

8
00:01:21,197 --> 00:01:23,000
The temple fair is in two weeks.

9
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,164
Gather at my house every day

10
00:01:24,164 --> 00:01:25,599
and rehearse for an hour.

11
00:01:25,599 --> 00:01:27,920
I'll send you home at night.

12
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,239
So...

13
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:30,320
let's start!

14
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:31,551
Okay.

15
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,763
This, this.

16
00:02:16,763 --> 00:02:18,640
[It's not a coincidence, I met you on purpose.]
This? I got it.

17
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,040
This, this, this.

18
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,680
- This?
- This, this.

19
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,116
Like this?

20
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:25,122
Is this right?

21
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,866
You're going on stage tomorrow.

22
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,979
Are you nervous?

23
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:38,087
More like a little upset.

24
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:41,439
If we're doomed to grow apart,

25
00:02:41,439 --> 00:02:43,243
we'd better not start.

26
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,199
A person is like an isle,

27
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:47,600
while his friends

28
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,619
are migratory birds that stay for a while.

29
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:53,560
In different seasons, some birds come,

30
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:55,280
and some leave.

31
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,680
The changing of seasons

32
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,314
is the law of nature.

33
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,076
An isle's persistence

34
00:03:01,076 --> 00:03:02,968
can't decide the departure and stay of birds.

35
00:03:04,432 --> 00:03:06,240
The process of being together matters more.

36
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,920
The outcome is not controllable.

37
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,617
No need to be attached.

38
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,483
Aren't you tired of talking this way?

39
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,278
What?

40
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:20,600
You put yourself down,

41
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,283
expecting others to contradict you

42
00:03:22,283 --> 00:03:24,355
with what you want to hear.

43
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,880
What do you think I want to hear?

44
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,280
Look,

45
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,960
we're all humans.

46
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,640
But some are isles,

47
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,268
and some are birds.

48
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,080
We can all be isles,

49
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,400
staying in the ocean,

50
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,879
or birds, flying around together,

51
00:03:48,879 --> 00:03:50,057
right?

52
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,080
That makes sense.

53
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,214
So...

54
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,472
good luck tomorrow.

55
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,812
Good luck.

56
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,224
Let's go.

57
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:34,800
<i>Hello?</i>

58
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,680
Hello.

59
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,612
<i>Nan Feng, it's me.</i>

60
00:04:38,386 --> 00:04:39,720
Mom.

61
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,504
<i>How have you been lately?</i>

62
00:04:42,225 --> 00:04:43,520
I'm fine.

63
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,790
<i>Nan Feng,</i>

64
00:04:45,825 --> 00:04:47,920
<i>your dad is in the City Hospital.</i>

65
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,760
<i>He'll have a surgery tomorrow night.</i>

66
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,767
<i>His wife and daughter aren't with him.</i>

67
00:04:53,221 --> 00:04:55,255
<i>So, what should we do?</i>

68
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:57,840
<i>He called me in such a case.</i>

69
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,505
<i>Why not earlier?</i>

70
00:04:59,505 --> 00:05:01,352
<i>Besides, we've been divorced for so long.</i>

71
00:05:01,352 --> 00:05:02,800
Just get to the point.

72
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:06,521
<i>Feng, can you go there?</i>

73
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,160
<i>It sounds like an inquiry,</i>

74
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,800
<i>but actually has a preset answer.</i>

75
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,466
<i>He just wants to look considerate.</i>

76
00:05:13,466 --> 00:05:15,125
<i>Isn't it sly?</i>

77
00:05:16,372 --> 00:05:17,840
[Nanwan Temple Fair]
[Fireworks Show]

78
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:19,966
I'm going to the city to see my dad.

79
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:25,160
What for?

80
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,360
He wants me to transfer to

81
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,079
the New Concept Writing Class in the city,

82
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:29,627
for more opportunities,

83
00:05:29,627 --> 00:05:30,879
the admission to the school team,

84
00:05:30,879 --> 00:05:32,680
provincial competitions

85
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,279
with bonuses and

86
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,600
extra points in the college entrance exam.

87
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,045
That's so sudden.

88
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:40,640
He called me out of the blue yesterday,

89
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,120
saying he wants me to study in the city.

90
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,720
I can board at school on weekdays,

91
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:46,519
and at his house on weekends.

92
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,560
Your dad is so strange.

93
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,908
Why is living at home called "board"?

94
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,253
When are you going?

95
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:57,472
In a few days.

96
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,519
He asked me to go

97
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:03,000
and get familiar with it first.

98
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,320
I'll stay until school starts.

99
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:07,345
Didn't we agree to go to
the temple fair together next month?

100
00:06:18,639 --> 00:06:20,160
I wanted to!

101
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,905
I just couldn't.

102
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,280
Congrats.

103
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:27,364
I'll buy you another Green Tongue popsicle.

104
00:06:42,101 --> 00:06:43,315
Here.

105
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:45,435
Eat up.

106
00:06:46,138 --> 00:06:48,320
The Walkman can be used for learning English.

107
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,818
Feel free to use.

108
00:06:52,392 --> 00:06:54,279
Make yourself at home.

109
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:56,120
Just like it's your own home.

110
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,920
I'll arrange my luggage first.

111
00:06:57,920 --> 00:06:59,820
No, no. I'll do it.

112
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,160
Hey, why don't you eat?

113
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:37,003
Don't be courteous with Dad.

114
00:07:41,541 --> 00:07:43,221
I forgot the spoon.

115
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,080
Here.

116
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:49,200
Here's a spoon.

117
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,520
Thank you...

118
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:52,676
Dad.

119
00:08:01,570 --> 00:08:03,560
- Are you back from shopping with your mom?
- Yes.

120
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,120
Say hi to your brother.

121
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:07,000
Isn't this my spoon?

122
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,279
He's just borrowing it.

123
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:10,760
It'll be fine once washed.

124
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,319
I don't want it anymore.

125
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:14,639
- Don't be childish.
- You're biased!

126
00:08:14,639 --> 00:08:16,759
It's my ice cream, my spoon,

127
00:08:16,759 --> 00:08:18,397
and my home!

128
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,323
You...

129
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,822
Here, take it.

130
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:32,840
Hurry, hurry, hurry! Go inside!

131
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:33,955
Oh.

132
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,341
Hey, honey.

133
00:08:42,341 --> 00:08:43,800
<i>Why are you blaming Yan Yan?</i>

134
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:44,919
<i>Married into my family,</i>

135
00:08:44,919 --> 00:08:46,720
<i>you brought him without permission.</i>

136
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,120
<i>Why are you taking care?</i>

137
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,580
<i>Is his mom dead?</i>

138
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:52,000
Can you keep it down?

139
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,680
He's in the house.

140
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,799
<i>Why do you fear a deaf guy?</i>

141
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:57,040
<i>If he feels wronged,</i>

142
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,084
<i>he can go live with his mom!</i>

143
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,519
Come and take a look at the vegetables.

144
00:09:22,519 --> 00:09:23,759
Come and take a look.

145
00:09:23,759 --> 00:09:25,399
Homegrown vegetables.

146
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:27,200
No pesticides.

147
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,759
Homegrown vegetables.

148
00:09:28,759 --> 00:09:30,320
No pesticides.

149
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,520
Why don't you shout?

150
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,440
Didn't you say you'd
help Grandma sell vegetables?

151
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,791
I have a cold and a sore throat.

152
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,279
What cold?

153
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:41,372
I think you're just timid.

154
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:43,600
Homegrown vegetables.

155
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,000
No pesticides.

156
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,255
Guaranteed healthy.

157
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:51,800
Homegrown... vegetables.

158
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,440
Reasonable prices.

159
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,919
Take your pick.

160
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:01,335
Fresh!

161
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:06,399
Fresh and delicious!

162
00:10:06,399 --> 00:10:07,840
Everyone, come buy!

163
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:10,200
Homegrown vegetables. No pesticides.

164
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,200
- Pick some. How much do you want?
- I'll help you.

165
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,600
Okay, weigh it for Grandma.

166
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,879
Okay.

167
00:10:14,879 --> 00:10:16,000
Homegrown vegetables.

168
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,159
No pesticides.

169
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:18,519
Guaranteed healthy.

170
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:20,130
Reasonable price.

171
00:10:20,915 --> 00:10:22,360
- Is this enough?
- Yes.

172
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:24,080
- Want it?
- Reasonable price.

173
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:26,640
Guaranteed healthy.

174
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,480
Here you go.

175
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:31,519
Can I wear it?

176
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:32,840
It's cute, Grandma.

177
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,932
Nice!

178
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,850
Here. How much do you want?

179
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,390
Look at this.

180
00:11:08,399 --> 00:11:10,480
Your brother is handsome.

181
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,519
Country bumpkin.

182
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:13,639
He won the grand writing prize in the city.

183
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:15,360
The principal of Ninth High School

184
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,676
promised my dad a huge sum

185
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:19,679
if he's admitted to
Tsinghua or Peking University

186
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:22,000
after studying there, for publicity.

187
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,639
Ninth High School has a poor admission rate.

188
00:11:23,639 --> 00:11:25,720
It has no writing class.

189
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:27,609
Anyway, none of my business.

190
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,207
Ren Xi Zhou.

191
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,280
What's wrong with you?

192
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:45,823
It's not even the end of the month,
and your phone bill is due.

193
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,519
Just SMS fees.

194
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:51,040
Missy, are you from a rich family?

195
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,759
It's charged per message!

196
00:11:52,759 --> 00:11:55,061
Don't send short ones!

197
00:11:55,061 --> 00:11:57,600
Mom, I want to buy a hat.

198
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,759
A branded one.

199
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:00,760
What else?

200
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,720
All you think about is dressing up.

201
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:04,305
Your dad...

202
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,960
Isn't Dad out doing business?

203
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,933
- When is he coming back?
- Why do you care?

204
00:12:12,279 --> 00:12:13,679
Buy one with your money.

205
00:12:13,679 --> 00:12:14,931
Thank you, Mom.

206
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,424
A fake one will do.

207
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,759
<i>How is it?</i>

208
00:13:08,759 --> 00:13:10,480
<i>What are you doing?</i>

209
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:11,800
<i>It's good.</i>

210
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:13,600
<i>I'm working on a problem.</i>

211
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,639
<i>Among the natural numbers from 1 to 200,</i>

212
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:18,600
<i>randomly select 101 numbers,</i>

213
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,360
<i>prove that there must be two numbers</i>

214
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,960
<i>where one is a multiple of the other.</i>

215
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,559
<i>So you're in your dad's house?</i>

216
00:13:25,559 --> 00:13:26,880
<i>Yes.</i>

217
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:30,280
<i>This community has the most acacia trees.</i>

218
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:33,600
<i>Yesterday, I found
a small acacia flower on the table.</i>

219
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:35,560
<i>It smelled like honey water.</i>

220
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,919
<i>Maybe... you'll like it.</i>

221
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,280
Give me your phone.

222
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,280
My classmates asked me questions.

223
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:48,559
I brought you here
despite my family's objection,

224
00:13:48,559 --> 00:13:51,480
for your education, not leisure!

225
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,987
Give me your phone!

226
00:13:54,640 --> 00:13:55,848
Give me!

227
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,271
Give me!

228
00:14:03,159 --> 00:14:04,287
Give me!

229
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,710
I'm your dad!

230
00:14:26,919 --> 00:14:29,190
<i>Are you coming to the temple fair next week?</i>

231
00:14:30,879 --> 00:14:32,005
<i>No.</i>

232
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:36,080
<i>Feng, are you listening?</i>

233
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,072
<i>Can you make it?</i>

234
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:43,770
<i>No.</i>
